Package edu.missouri.WorldBankModelBuilder Description

Contains classes to build economic models using World Bank data
Version:
0.09 2016-04-27

Version history

Ver# date Changes
0.09 2016-04-27 Added support for the Smets-Woulters economic model as a temporary fix to not being able to read domain knowledge from files:
  • added ModelClusterizer#buildSWModel(java.util.Map)
  • added %lt;use Unesco model> parameter to ModelClusterizer#main(String[])
  • added ReconstructionTest#getSWTitles()
  • added ReconstructionTest#buildSWModel(java.util.Map)
  • added ReconstructionTest#buildEmptySWModel(java.util.Map)
  • added ReconstructionTest#constructSWToFile(weka.core.Instances, String, int)
  • added ReconstructionTest#constructEmptySWToFile(weka.core.Instances, String, int)
  • added %lt;use Unesco model> parameter to ModelClusterizer#main(String[])
(ModelClusterizer is now version 0.06 ReconstructionTest is now version 0.05)
0.08 2016-04-25 ReconstructionTest#main(String[]) now sends summary statistics to a specified CSV (ReconstructionTest is now version 0.04)
0.07 2016-04-25 ReconstructionTest#main(String[]) now skips countries with insufficient data to discretize (Previously, a compatibility error was thrown) (ReconstructionTest is now version 0.03)
0.06 2016-04-25 Bugfixes; ModelClusterizer#shiftBy(java.util.List, int) now uses NaN instead of null as the filter element for compatibility with Weka. (ModelClusterizer is now version 0.05; ReconstructionTest is now version 0.02)
0.05 2016-04-24 Added ReconstructionTest
0.04 2016-04-19 Added ModelClusterizer#buildUnescoModel(java.util.Map) ModelClusterizer now allows specifying the output directory
0.03 2016-04-19 ModelClusterizer now stores in ./out/nets
0.02 2016-04-19 Bug fixes
0.01 2016-04-19 Package created with ModelClusterizer
